@NODE "ABOUT" "What is Node-Status ?"
                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}

Node-status v1.0 is a small utility to show which node you're logged onto.
It also report the baudrate of the connection and the current status on each
of the other available nodes.

Node-Status can also be used to display a logo-textfile (with MCI-support)
to the users together with the node-status report.


The main reason why I coded this door is that most of the doors available lacks
a good design, and do not have any textfile support.

I also included a Clear-Screen argument for those who wants to get rid of that
"modem-report" message from AmiExpress at the top of the screen.


The door is also in my opinion more powerful than other doors available. 
First of all, it has a very nice tool-type support. This is very important when
you want a correct node baudrate directly out from each individual node-icon. 
No incorrect-status from the /X-port is being used for this purpose. 



Finally,


This utility is coded in Amiga-E with inline-ASM for maximal speed-performance!
@ENDNODE



;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



@NODE "REQUIRE" "Requirements to run this door."
                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}


You will need a computer with OS 2.x, or higher, and any version of AmiExpress.
However, AmiExpress v4.xx++ is preferred.


Node-Status also requires the AEDoor.Library present in LIBS:. You can find this
library in the LIBS-directory in this package.

If this library is not present for some reason in this package, then give my
board a call and I'll gladly give it to you.

@ENDNODE



;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



@NODE "INSTALL" "How to do the installation..."
                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}

All you have to do is to copy each of the files in this archive to its
belonging directory under "BBS:".

That's all... (Simple isn't it? :)



Configuration :
---------------

There is only one way to configurate this door, and that is through the
Node-Status.info icon. If you, from workbench, use information on this icon,
you'll see two Tooltype choices in use. These are : 


CLEAR_SCREEN=YES
SHOW_LOGO=YES


These choices can be toggled by writing YES or NO. (Not case-sensitive)


The first one will clear the screen right after the modem-handshake is over,
and the second one will show the textfile : "Node-status.Logo".


* The logo-textfile must be placed in the same directory as the main-program.

@ENDNODE



